<subSubSection id="7D0F63B1F46605F4507BF28401C81641" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E24D1E24A14F8F6306B5FD86AD477F67" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="15BE10A888737FBD1B587B09A320063D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Lower slopes of Sierra El Aguaje in desert scrub on rocky slopes near sea level in NW Mexico.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91A9331BC8B71401C2970ACCBA6EBCBB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="AD1D1FE93CD147CB8AB8A11061FB3AAB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">MEXICO. Sonora</emphasis>
: San Carlos Bay-Catch-22 airstrip, 
<emphasis id="5C0BAE7E1EB4E6453929A4854EB88ED1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T.F. Daniel</emphasis>
2360 (ASU, CAS).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="34F521193939B41E1B064DE883919F07" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="07A33E1EBA762C662109C1813299DE57" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9386CF46CE80D6A35639611120F9506D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The holotype was cited as deposited in UA, a non-existent herbarium code. It was apparently intended to refer to the University of Arizona (ARIZ).</paragraph>
